<div class="section_title">2005 International CES Attracts Most Influential Array of Media in Show History </div>
<span class="text">
The 2005 International CES set media coverage and international media attendance records again. Through a year-round media outreach campaign, the 2005 International CES attracted more than 4,500 media outlets&nbsp;from 48 countries. These results stand on par with the 2004 show even as CES instituted more stringent media registration criteria to focus on media quality over quantity. 
<P>The show set a few new media records for media attendance and coverage, including: </P>
<UL>
<LI>the number of international media (up nine percent, with 890 media). </LI>
<LI>the number of analysts (up 20 percent, to more than 2,200 financial and industry analysts). </LI>
<LI>Overall show coverage (up about five percent, to more than 3,000 articles and stories). </LI>
<LI>Japanese coverage increased more than 20 percent, as we generated 790 articles and stories in Japanese media, ranking the country first in coverage outside the U.S. </LI></UL>
<P>In addition, the 2005 International CES was covered by national outlets such as AP, Reuters, <EM>Wall Street Journal</EM>, <EM>Investor’s Business Daily</EM>, <EM>USA Today</EM>, <EM>Financial Times</EM>, and <EM>Forbes</EM> and the national editions for the <EM>Los Angeles Times</EM>, <EM>New York Times</EM> and <EM>Washington Post</EM>. Top national broadcast networks such as ABC, CBS, CNN, CNBC, MSNBC, NBC and NPR also covered the 2005 International CES. </P>
<P>Cable and broadcast television carried extensive live and taped coverage of the show nationwide, including programs such as <EM>CBS Sunday Morning News</EM>, <EM>ESPN’s Cold Pizza</EM> and <EM>CNN Headline News</EM>. In addition to the cable and broadcast coverage, the 2005 International CES b-roll was used by 334 local TV stations across the country reaching an estimated audience of 10,661,895 via 489 telecasts. More than 200 leading magazines, business, consumer and trade publications were on-site covering the events that transpired, reaching more than 150 million readers. </P>
<P>And the show’s international coverage continues to grow. In addition to the great coverage in Japan, we saw increased coverage in China, Korea, Europe and Mexico.</P>
</span>
