    <p><strong>Bring Your Dreams to Life with Our Vision</strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    Like the legendary aspirations of Martin Luther King, Jr., I have a dream. It hinges around the success of each CES exhibitor above and beyond the actual trade show each January.
<P>If my dream came to life, you and each of our 2,500+ exhibitors would report year-over-year growth and endless opportunities to put your story into the hands of the industry movers and shakers.</P>
<P>So I’m constantly thinking of ways to make that dream a reality for us all. In my sleep, in my car, at my desk; it’s always there. And it occurred to me that a solid vision could, in fact, spur this dream along. <EM>Consumer Electronics Vision</EM>, that is.</P>
<P>The official publication of the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA), <EM>CE Vision </EM>is the only publication to circulate deep within the consumer electronics industry, from manufacturing to retail. <EM>CE Vision</EM> drills down to precisely what top management needs to know to make sound business decisions.</P>
<P>For advertisers, <EM>CE Vision </EM>is a&nbsp; straight path to the people within the industry that design, develop, manufacture, buy and distribute audio, video, mobile electronics, wireless and landline communications, IT, home networking, multimedia, accessory products and related services sold through consumer channels.</P>
<P>In addition to the great advertising opportunities, there’s also still time to keep pitching your post-CES stories.</P>
<P>While the news dailies and broadcast news have banked most of their CES stories by now, the trade and consumer monthlies are still going strong.&nbsp; For example, CEA’s <EM>CE Vision</EM> magazine is featuring three top stories in its <A href="http://www.ce.org/publications/vision/" target=_blank>March-April issue</A>:</P>
<UL>
<LI>Point Counterpoint: Blue Ray Vs. HD-DVD </LI>
<LI>Networking Home Entertainment&nbsp; </LI>
<LI>Post-CES Show Coverage</LI></UL>
<P><EM>CE Vision </EM>reaches 23,000 industry manufacturers, retailers and business developers – basically taking the core CES attendee audience and delivering t-industry news six times a year right to their offices. This award-winning magazine circulates to the most established and successful businesses in the CE market. <BR>&nbsp;<BR>In May/June, look for <EM>CE Vision </EM>stories on:</P>
<UL>
<LI>USB Flash Drives and Storage Drive Devices&nbsp; </LI>
<LI>Changing Distribution Channels </LI>
<LI>What’s Next for Digital Imaging?</LI></UL>
<P>In July/August, <EM>CE Vision </EM>profiles:</P>
<UL>
<LI>The Hybrid Car&nbsp; </LI>
<LI>HDTV Advances&nbsp; </LI>
<LI>Digital Audio </LI></UL>
<P>For editorial pitches, contact Publisher/Editor-in-Chief Cindy Stevens at (703) 907-7609, <A href="mailto:cstevens@CE.org">cstevens@CE.org</A>.&nbsp; For <EM>CE Vision </EM>advertising, check out the issue online&nbsp;or contact NAPCO Senior Vice President of Sales and Marketing Rick Albuck at (215) 238-5215, <A href="mailto:rickalbuck@napco.com">rickalbuck@napco.com</A>.</P>
<P>Use our <EM>Vision</EM> to make your dreams—and mine—come true.</P>
